quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,49,"And [recall] when We saved you [i.e., your forefathers] from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with the worst torment, slaughtering your [newborn] sons and keeping your females alive. And in that was a great trial from your Lord."
  2,50,"And [recall] when We parted the sea for you and saved you and drowned the people of Pharaoh while you were looking on."
  2,51,"And [recall] when We made an appointment with Moses for forty nights. Then you took [for worship] the calf after him [i.e., his departure], while you were wrongdoers."